# the [[color]] [[crimson]], a [[vivid]] [[red]] edging towards [[pink]]
#: {{syn|ja|紅色|tr=kurenai-iro, kōshoku, beni-iro|丹紅|tr2=tankō}}
#* {{RQ:Manyoshu|19|4139}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man19Yo.html#4139 here]
#*: {{ja-usex|m=春%苑 '''紅'''尓保布 桃%花 下照道%尓 出立%𡢳嬬|m_kana=はるの%その '''くれなゐ'''にほふ ももの%はな したでるみち%に いでたつ%をとめ|春 の 園 '''紅''' にほふ 桃 の 花 下%照る 道 に 出で立つ 娘子|はる の その '''くれなゐ''' にほふ もも の はな した%でる みち に いでたつ をとめ|rom=haru no sono '''kurenai''' niou momo no hana shitaderu michi ni idetatsu otome|My whole spring arbor radiates a '''crimson''' glow: blossoms of the peach shine down on the garden path where a maiden steps in view.<ref>{{cite-book|1998|Edwin A. Cranston|The Gem-Glistening Cup|edition=illustrated|publisher=Stanford University Press|isbn=0-8047-3157-8|page=466}}</ref>|sort=くれない}}
# the [[safflower]] (''[[Carthamus tinctorius]]''), from which this color is [[extract]]ed
#: {{syn|ja|呉の藍|tr=Kure no ai|紅花|tr2=kōka, benibana|末摘花|tr3=suetsumuhana}}
#* '''905''', ''{{w|Kokin Wakashū}}'' (book 13, poem 661)
#*: {{ja-usex|'''紅'''の色にはいでじ隠れ沼の下にかよひて恋は死ぬとも|'''くれなゐ''' の いろ に は いでじ かくれ-ぬ の した に かよひて こひ は しぬ と も|rom='''kurenai''' no iro ni wa ideji kakure nu no shita ni kayoite koi wa shinu to mo|I shall not show it as a '''safflower''' flaunts its red―not though I perish of a love kept as secret as streams in a hidden marsh.<ref>{{cite-book|1985|Helen Craig McCullough|Brocade by Night: ''Kokin Wakashū'' and the Court Style in Japanese Classical Poetry|publisher=Stanford University Press|isbn=0-8047-6645-2|page=264}}</ref>}}

